### Auth endpoints
# Passwordless admin login: request an OTP by email, then exchange the OTP for a JWT.
# Requires the VS Code "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client).
# Click "Send Request" above each request.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@adminEmail = your-admin@email.com

### 1. Request an OTP
# Only the email set as ADMIN_EMAIL in .env is allowed.
# In dev (no working Plunk key) the OTP is printed to the server console.
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{adminEmail}}"
}

### 2. Verify the OTP -> returns a JWT
# Replace 123456 with the OTP from your email (or the server console).
# The returned token is reused automatically by projects.rest via the shared variable below.
# @name verifyOtp
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{adminEmail}}",
  "otp": "123456"
}

###
# After a successful verify, copy the "token" from the response and paste it into
# the @token variable at the top of projects.rest (or use {{verifyOtp.response.body.token}}
# within this same file).
